{
  "texts": [
    "Still, the possibility of a misdiagnosis 16 See Floridi (2023) for an up-to-date overview of different (legal) definitions of AI.",
    "17 https://legalinstruments.oecd.org/en/instruments/OECD-LEGAL-0449.",
    "Note that this is not the only possible definition of AI, not even if we narrow it down to legal definitions.",
    "The AI Act, for example, defines an AI system as \"a machine-based system designed to operate with varying levels of autonomy, that may exhibit adaptiveness after deployment and that, for explicit or implicit objectives, infers, from the input it receives, how to generate outputs such as predictions, content, recommendations, or decisions that can influence physical or virtual environments\" (Art. 3, 1).",
    "is open, with potential life-threatening consequences for the patients."
  ]
}